Feature: the canonical lead CLAUDE.md primer directs the router to proactively initiate a product-discovery conversation when it detects an effectively-empty repo, instead of declaring idle

  lead-vglj (P2) — product authority 2026-06-29 (verbatim): "for the lead to
  detect when the repo is effectively empty and start a product discovery
  conversation with the user to start determining the shape of the new system."

  This scenario pins the PROACTIVE-INITIATION half: on detecting the
  effectively-empty / no-product-defined state (defined by sibling scenario, file
  221) at session start or during the idle-detection checklist, the router must
  OPEN a product-discovery conversation with the product authority rather than
  declaring idle and waiting for a prompt. This is the empty-repo TRIGGER that
  FIRES the existing product-authority discovery gate.

  Design alignment (reference, do not contradict): the existing product-authority
  discovery gate already establishes that the discovery DIALOGUE happens at the
  main-agent / router level because discovery subagents are non-interactive and
  cannot conduct it. This scenario adds the trigger that fires that dialogue
  proactively; it must NOT pin a non-interactive subagent doing the talking. The
  discovery skill furniture (jobs-to-be-done, problem-framing-canvas,
  opportunity-solution-tree, customer-journey-map) exists; the trigger leads the
  router into a discovery conversation seeded from that furniture, capturing the
  result as the seed brief / intent.

  AUTHORING ONLY — no BC dispatch. @bc tag is the Architect's to apply at
  assignment time; @lead_integration:templates below is provisional placement
  matching sibling primer-furniture scenarios.

@lead_integration:templates
  @scenario_hash:eb64adc52ce02579
  Scenario: the canonical lead primer directs the router, on the effectively-empty state at session start or the idle-detection checkpoint, to proactively open a product-discovery conversation rather than declare idle
    Given the "shop-templates" package ships a canonical "CLAUDE.md" primer template for shop type "lead" through its public template-access surface
    And the lead repo is in the effectively-empty / no-product-defined state
    When I ask the package for that canonical primer body for shop type "lead"
    Then a non-empty template body is returned
    And the returned body contains a contiguous block directing the router, on detecting the effectively-empty state at session start or during the idle-detection checklist, to proactively open a product-discovery conversation with the product authority
    And that block states the discovery conversation is conducted at the main-agent / router level — consistent with the product-authority discovery gate — and is not delegated to a non-interactive discovery subagent
    And that block names seeding the conversation from the discovery skill furniture, such as jobs-to-be-done, problem-framing-canvas, or opportunity-solution-tree, and capturing the result as the seed brief or intent
    And that block states that on the effectively-empty state the router initiates discovery rather than declaring idle
